---
title: French Dip Beef Sandwiches with Onion Gravy and a Green Salad
description: The French Dip is built around three things: good, crusty bread; a meaty filling; and a side of gravy for dunking the whole thing into—in other words, it’s the epitome of comfort food. And if you like your food moist and dripping with juices, it’s a dream come true. After you’ve caramelized some onion, sizzled the beef, and simmered the gravy ’til it’s thick and saucy, we think you’ll agree that it’s 100 percent amazingness in sandwich form.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/french-dip-beef-sandwiches-c5e99b94.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/french-dip-beef-sandwiches-5a0dd97b7901f92d80720b72-83aeaf5a.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/french-dip-beef-sandwiches-5a0dd97b7901f92d80720b72
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 20m
nutrition:
  calories: 800 kcal
  fat: 45 g
  saturated fat: 20 g
  carbohydrates: 59 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1150 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and slice @yellow onion{1}. Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in
a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, tossing, until lightly browned,
~{1-2%minutes}. Lower heat to medium and toss in 1 tsp @bold & savory steak spice{1%tsp}.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, tossing, until very soft and browned,
~{4-5%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in another large pan over medium-high heat.
Pat @beef stir-fry{10%oz} dry with a #paper towel{}, then season all over with
@salt{}, @pepper{}, and remaining @bold & savory steak spice{1%tbsp}. Add to pan and
cook, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes}. Remove
from pan and set aside.

Transfer cooked onion to pan used for beef over medium-high heat. Stir in 1 cup of
water and @beef stock concentrate{1}, scraping up any browned bits on bottom. Bring
to a simmer, then lower heat to medium. Cook until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.
Remove from heat.

Cut @demi-baguette{2} in half lengthwise. Sprinkle ¼ of the @Italian cheese blend{1/2%cup}
onto one baguette bottom, then top with half the beef and another ¼ of the cheese.
Remove some onion slices from gravy and arrange on top, then cover with a baguette
top to make sandwich. Repeat with remaining baguette and fillings.

> It's OK if you don't use all the onions.

Wipe out pan used for onions, then melt @butter{1%tbsp} in it over medium-low heat.
Add sandwiches and toast until golden, ~{1-2%minutes} per side.

> Press down on the sandwiches as they toast—try using a heavy pan to keep them flat.

While sandwiches toast, halve @lemon{1}. Toss @mixed greens{2%oz} in a #medium bowl{}
with a large drizzle @olive oil{2%tsp} and squeeze or two of lemon. Season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Divide sandwiches and salad between plates. Divide gravy between two
#small bowls{} and serve on the side for dipping sandwiches into.